summary: Villanelle and pink. -The colour pink is overall a warm colour. It usually represents love and romance. Also it is seen to be...
caption:
Villanelle and pink.

-The colour pink is overall a warm colour. It usually represents love and romance. Also it is seen to be ‘feminine.’ It also has bright and varied different shades.

Villanelle, while she is rather cold and lacks compassion, often wears pink. It may seem like a strange choice however there are a few reasons as to why. For a start; she has a playful side. Whether it’s using Eve’s toothbrush or dressing up as Konstantin for his birthday, she likes to have fun in her own way. As mentioned, pink is considered to be a 'girls colour’ And Villanelle certainly knows how to use her feminine charms to get what she wants. Pink to make the boys (and girls) wink, maybe? Another option is how bright and loud it can be. She is no wallflower. She likes to make a statement and keep all eyes on her. Perhaps that’s why?

…Then again, the woman may just like the fucking colour.

summary: Guys. I love Killing Eve so much, but...what in the goddamn hell are they doing with Carolyn, Kenny, Konstantin, Jess, and Hugo?...
body: Guys. I love Killing Eve so much, but…what in the goddamn hell are they doing with Carolyn, Kenny, Konstantin, Jess, and Hugo? They seem to be really intent on just having Carolyn do weird shit. For no purpose. Just every time she shows up she’s doing something odd and for some reason she’s doing nothing in terms of actually investigating. And who are Jess and Hugo? No, really, who are these people? They feel like props or something, just like floating around the office being pregnant and gay, just fucking vibing. I. Don’t. Understand. Can these characters get an actual storylines or am I supposed to pretend like I care about Niko?
